If you want to use a library in Maven you should add the dependency to your project, there is no need to hunt for all transitive dependencies (unless the docs say otherwise). For the world wind I found the dependency on this site: [https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/gov.nasa/worldwind/2.0.0-986][1]

    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;gov.nasa&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;worldwind&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;2.0.0-986&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

It should work.

One of the advantages of using Maven is that there is no need to know every jar needed to use every library, Maven will manage this. In this case, the World Wind Maven dependency has it&#39;s own POM that declares all needed dependencies. Maven will scan all POMs from all dependencies and will download all required JARs when needed. 

  [1]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/gov.nasa/worldwind/2.0.0-986

